        <scopecontent encodinganalog="520$a">
            <head>Scope and Content </head>
            <p>Mary Stone, widow of William Stone, leases Pain a messuage consisting of a house,
                shop and slaughterhouse for the term of thirty years. Pain may vacate at the end of
                seven, four teen or twenty-one years with six months' notice. The rent is 18N a
                year, payable quarterly. The tenement is in Waltham Holy Cross, Essex. A list of
                fixtures to remain with the property is included. Witnessed by Oliver Cromwell and
                John Harrison, Million Bank, London. </p>
        </scopecontent>
